ROCKET SOCKS chased the field along the rail into the turn, then rallied in late stretch but it wasn't enough. COOL RIDE was in a hard drive to stalk the leader from the three path throughout the turn then flattened out in the stretch. POUND OUT A DEAL raced in close behind the leader along the rail , then checked, and had no final bid in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 2 1 1/16M Turf CR: 87. Claiming Purse 23000. (PLUS UP TO $4,800 Open ATB) FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE NOVEMBER 11, 2022 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000. Texas Bred Claiming Pri ce $30,000. (If Deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the Turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile and One Sixteenth.) (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LIL ASHLEY B. bumped away from the gate by DISCREET SMILE causing DEL MAR DRAMA to be shut off at the start, settled into stride near the rear of the field for the first half mile, closed ground along the fence, waited for racing room at the head of the lane, finally found room along the rail and closed with a rush to be going away late as much best. DISCREET SMILE broke outward impeding rivals, took the lead into the first turn, dropped back off the rank pace presser to stalk, finished gamely to rally down the lane to hold the place. DADDYMADEMEDOIT tracked the pace from a comfortable spot along the rail for a half mile, angled out to challenge from three wide in the turn and finished well in the drive to just miss the place. HOT TUB HOTTIE raced wide into the first turn resisting the rating of the rider, moved to the lead down the backside while still rank, cleared the field by open lengths in the far turn and flattened out coming for home. XYLOPHONE trailed the field to the far turn, swung out for the drive to mount a belated rally to be gaining nearing the wire. DEL MAR DRAMA was shut off leaving the gate bumping hard to drop to the back of the field, made an early move down the backside to be prominent and flattened out turning for home.

ENTRY.COMMENT: broke outward, shut off rivals, led, rated, finished gamely

ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped strart, rail trip, patient handling, closed w/rush

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 3 1M Dirt CR: 86. Claiming Purse 13500. (PLUS UP TO $2,700 Open ATB) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE AT A MILE OR OVER SINCE DECEMBER 1, 2022 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000. Texas Bred Claiming Price $6,250.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: KENTUCKY PEERLESS lead the way into the first turn to set the pace down the backstretch from the inside, cleared the far turn then drew off in the early stretch to win by many and proved best in the end. BIG ROJO chased the pace while two wide, was moving up swiftly on the far turn to duel for the place position while tussling with inner rival, continued to dig in gamely and was up at the wire. HE'S PRETTY LUCKY settled along the inside the first half of the course then, bid on the far turn to rally in the early stretch, drifted out and brushed rival while competing for he place position down the lane but missed in the end. GOLD ACCOUNT settled back in the two path while racing down the backstretch and into the far turn, then rallied in the early stretch to close well. PEPPERMAN chased the pace from the inside, made a mild bid on the far turn then flattened out in the stretch. FREDONIAN stalked the pace while two wide down the backstretch and into the turn, then rallied in the early stretch while drifting out six wide then gave way in the end. MAX PANDOWDY was off slowly then raced behind the field, slowly losing ground throughout and was no factor. There was a STEWARD'S INQUIRY in regards to the stretch run, After review there was no change made to the order of finish.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 4 1 1/8M Turf CR: 105. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 22000. (PLUS UP TO $4,400 Open ATB) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $15,000 OR LESS SINCE MAY 11, 2021 OR CLAIMING PRICE $25,000. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since A pril 13 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000 (Races Where Entered For $20,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances). (If Deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the Turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile and One Eighth.) (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ENGLANDER settled in to track the run away pacesetter from second, moved to challenge entering the turn, dueled from between horses to upper stretch, dueled with the runner-up through the lane and pulled just clear late in a game effort. DON'TASK DON'TTELL reserved in hand for the first half mile while always in striking position, moved up three wide into the turn to engage the leaders, battled with the winner to deep stretch and was out-finished to be second best. BROCK ON BY sped to the lead straightening out down the lane the first time, took clear command into the first turn, widened his lead to open lengths down the backside, responded well to the challenges through the turn to deep stretch and weakened late in the drive. KOKOKOMO settled in hand off the pace to be near the rear of the pack along the fence, moved up the rail in the far turn and launched a belated rally down the lane. JOHAN ZOFFANI (IRE) saved ground to creep into contention nearing the turn along the rail, lacked racing room turning for home, swung into the clear mid-stretch and finished willingly. THUNDERSHOOK raced three wide through the first turn, raced mid-pack throughout and went evenly failing to mount a bid. HARD LOVE trailed to midway on the turn and passed tiring rivals in the stretch. ALVAARO was rank for a half mile never settling into stride and was finished early. NEWPORT BEACH was well placed to track the pacesetter in the first flight and gave way in the final bend.

Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. (Preference To Horses That Have Not Started For $20,000 Or Less In Their Last 3 Starts).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SMARTY RIDGE settled off the early pacesetters, swung out five wide at the top of the lane and closed with a strong drive to be up in time. TIZ BODHI BOY well in hand to be near the rear of the field, commenced a rally at the top of the stretch and closed with a belated rush splitting horses to gain the place. DADA BOOM RIDGE raced a the rear of the main body of the field and was never a factor. SUMMER HELP well placed for the first half mile and tired in the stretch. KEEPMOVINGFORWARD made a left turn from the gate, was gathered up after spotting the field nearly fifty lengths, galloped to the top of the lane and worked through the lane.
